@startuml FoodOrderingSystem_Annotated

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam enum {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Food Ordering System - Class Diagram (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "User searches 'pizza', sorts by rating, adds to cart, places order, pays, tracks delivery, rates restaurant."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class FoodOrderingService <<Facade>> {
    - restaurants : Map<String, Restaurant>
    - orders : Map<String, Order>
    - users : Map<String, Customer>
    - searchStrategy : SearchStrategy
    - sortStrategy : SortStrategy
    - paymentService : PaymentService
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    - ratingService : RatingService
    --
    + searchRestaurants(criteria) : List<Restaurant>
    + sortResults(restaurants, strategy) : List<Restaurant>
    + placeOrder(cart, customerId, payStrategy) : Order
    + cancelOrder(orderId) : void
    + trackOrder(orderId) : OrderStatus
    + rateRestaurant(orderId, score, review) : Rating
    + registerCustomer(name, email, addr) : Customer
}

note top of FoodOrderingService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "User opens the app. Client only calls
    this **Facade**. It coordinates search,
    sort, ordering, payment, tracking,
    and rating — all behind one API."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: USER + RESTAURANT + MENU MODELS
' ====================================================================
class Customer {
    - customerId : String
    - name : String
    - email : String
    - phone : String
    - addresses : List<Address>
    - orderHistory : List<Order>
    --
    + getDefaultAddress() : Address
    + addAddress(addr) : void
}

class Address {
    - street : String
    - city : String
    - zipCode : String
    - latitude : double
    - longitude : double
    --
    + distanceTo(other) : double
}

class Restaurant {
    - restaurantId : String
    - name : String
    - cuisine : CuisineType
    - address : Address
    - menu : List<MenuItem>
    - averageRating : double
    - totalRatings : int
    - isOpen : boolean
    - avgDeliveryTimeMin : int
    --
    + getMenu() : List<MenuItem>
    + isOpen() : boolean
    + getAverageRating() : double
    + updateRating(newScore) : void
}

class MenuItem {
    - itemId : String
    - name : String
    - description : String
    - price : double
    - category : MenuCategory
    - isAvailable : boolean
    - isVegetarian : boolean
    --
    + getPrice() : double
    + isAvailable() : boolean
}

enum CuisineType {
    ITALIAN
    CHINESE
    INDIAN
    MEXICAN
    JAPANESE
    AMERICAN
}

enum MenuCategory {
    APPETIZER
    MAIN_COURSE
    DESSERT
    BEVERAGE
    SIDES
}

note left of Restaurant #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Core models.**
    "**Customer** with addresses.
    **Restaurant** has name, cuisine,
    menu, rating, deliveryTime.
    **MenuItem** has price, category,
    availability. Each class = one job."
    **(SRP)**
end note

Customer *-- Address : has >
Restaurant --> CuisineType
Restaurant --> Address : located at >
Restaurant *-- MenuItem : serves >
MenuItem --> MenuCategory


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: SEARCH — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class SearchCriteria {
    - query : String
    - cuisineType : CuisineType
    - location : Address
    - maxDistanceKm : double
    - maxPrice : double
    - vegetarianOnly : boolean
}

interface SearchStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + search(restaurants, criteria) : List<Restaurant>
}

class NameSearchStrategy {
    --
    + search(restaurants, criteria) : List<Restaurant>
}

class CuisineSearchStrategy {
    --
    + search(restaurants, criteria) : List<Restaurant>
}

class LocationSearchStrategy {
    - maxDistanceKm : double
    --
    + search(restaurants, criteria) : List<Restaurant>
}

class CompositeSearchStrategy {
    - strategies : List<SearchStrategy>
    --
    + search(restaurants, criteria) : List<Restaurant>
}

note bottom of SearchStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 3 - User searches "pizza".**
    "How do we find matching restaurants?
    **Strategy Pattern** — search logic is pluggable.
    **NameSearch**: fuzzy match on name/menu items.
    **CuisineSearch**: filter by cuisine type.
    **LocationSearch**: within X km radius."

    "**CompositeSearch** chains strategies:
    name match AND within 5km AND cuisine=Italian.
    Add PopularitySearch? One new class."
    **Pattern: Strategy + Composite | OCP, DIP**
end note

SearchStrategy <|.. NameSearchStrategy
SearchStrategy <|.. CuisineSearchStrategy
SearchStrategy <|.. LocationSearchStrategy
SearchStrategy <|.. CompositeSearchStrategy
CompositeSearchStrategy o--> SearchStrategy : chains >
FoodOrderingService --> SearchStrategy : delegates >
SearchCriteria --> CuisineType


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: SORT — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface SortStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + sort(restaurants) : List<Restaurant>
}

class SortByRating {
    - ascending : boolean
    --
    + sort(restaurants) : List<Restaurant>
}

class SortByPrice {
    - ascending : boolean
    --
    + sort(restaurants) : List<Restaurant>
}

class SortByDistance {
    - userLocation : Address
    --
    + sort(restaurants) : List<Restaurant>
}

class SortByDeliveryTime {
    --
    + sort(restaurants) : List<Restaurant>
}

class CompositeSortStrategy {
    - strategies : List<SortStrategy>
    --
    + sort(restaurants) : List<Restaurant>
}

note bottom of SortStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - Sort the results.**
    "Search returned 20 restaurants.
    How to rank them?"

    "**Strategy Pattern** again — sort is pluggable.
    **SortByRating**: highest rated first.
    **SortByPrice**: cheapest first.
    **SortByDistance**: nearest first.
    **SortByDeliveryTime**: fastest first."

    "**CompositeSortStrategy**: sort by rating,
    then by distance as tiebreaker."
    **Pattern: Strategy + Composite | OCP**
end note

SortStrategy <|.. SortByRating
SortStrategy <|.. SortByPrice
SortStrategy <|.. SortByDistance
SortStrategy <|.. SortByDeliveryTime
SortStrategy <|.. CompositeSortStrategy
CompositeSortStrategy o--> SortStrategy : chains >
FoodOrderingService --> SortStrategy : delegates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: CART + ORDER + BUILDER
' ====================================================================
class Cart {
    - customerId : String
    - restaurant : Restaurant
    - items : List<CartItem>
    --
    + addItem(menuItem, qty, instructions) : void
    + removeItem(itemId) : void
    + updateQuantity(itemId, qty) : void
    + getTotal() : double
    + clear() : void
    + getItems() : List<CartItem>
}

class CartItem {
    - menuItem : MenuItem
    - quantity : int
    - specialInstructions : String
    - customizations : List<String>
    --
    + getSubtotal() : double
}

class Order {
    - orderId : String
    - customer : Customer
    - restaurant : Restaurant
    - items : List<CartItem>
    - currentState : OrderState
    - status : OrderStatus
    - totalAmount : double
    - deliveryAddress : Address
    - deliveryAgent : DeliveryAgent
    - placedAt : LocalDateTime
    - observers : List<OrderObserver>
    --
    + confirm() : void
    + startPreparing() : void
    + dispatchForDelivery(agent) : void
    + markDelivered() : void
    + cancel(reason) : void
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    + notifyObservers() : void
}

enum OrderStatus {
    PLACED
    CONFIRMED
    PREPARING
    OUT_FOR_DELIVERY
    DELIVERED
    CANCELLED
}

class DeliveryAgent {
    - agentId : String
    - name : String
    - phone : String
    - currentLocation : Address
    - isAvailable : boolean
}

note top of Order #FFCDD2
    **STEP 5 - User places order.**
    "Cart items become an Order. Order is the
    **central domain object**. Has customer,
    restaurant, items, total, delivery address.
    Uses **State** (lifecycle) and
    **Observer** (notifications)."
end note

Cart *-- CartItem : contains >
CartItem --> MenuItem : for item >
Order --> Customer : ordered by >
Order --> Restaurant : from >
Order --> CartItem : contains >
Order --> OrderStatus
Order --> Address : deliver to >
Order --> DeliveryAgent : assigned to >
Customer --> Cart : owns >

class OrderBuilder <<Builder>> {
    - customer : Customer
    - restaurant : Restaurant
    - items : List<CartItem>
    - deliveryAddress : Address
    --
    + fromCart(cart) : OrderBuilder
    + customer(cust) : OrderBuilder
    + deliverTo(addr) : OrderBuilder
    + build() : Order
}

note bottom of OrderBuilder #D1C4E9
    **Builder for order creation.**
    "new OrderBuilder()
      .fromCart(cart)
      .customer(alice)
      .deliverTo(homeAddr)
      .build()"
    **Pattern: Builder | SRP**
end note

OrderBuilder --> Order : builds >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: STATE PATTERN — Order Lifecycle
' ====================================================================
interface OrderState <<State>> {
    + confirm(order) : void
    + startPreparing(order) : void
    + dispatch(order, agent) : void
    + deliver(order) : void
    + cancel(order, reason) : void
}

class PlacedState {
    + confirm(order) : void
    + cancel(order, reason) : void
}

class ConfirmedState {
    + startPreparing(order) : void
    + cancel(order, reason) : void
}

class PreparingState {
    + dispatch(order, agent) : void
    + cancel(order, reason) : void
}

class OutForDeliveryState {
    + deliver(order) : void
}

class DeliveredState {
    ' terminal state
}

class CancelledState {
    ' terminal state
}

note bottom of OrderState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 6 - Order moves through states.**
    "**State Pattern** — each state is a class.
    **PlacedState**: restaurant can confirm/cancel.
    **ConfirmedState**: kitchen starts preparing.
    **PreparingState**: done cooking, dispatch rider.
    **OutForDelivery**: rider delivers.
    **Delivered/Cancelled**: terminal."

    Placed -> Confirmed -> Preparing
    -> OutForDelivery -> Delivered
    Placed/Confirmed/Preparing -> Cancelled
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

OrderState <|.. PlacedState
OrderState <|.. ConfirmedState
OrderState <|.. PreparingState
OrderState <|.. OutForDeliveryState
OrderState <|.. DeliveredState
OrderState <|.. CancelledState
Order --> OrderState : delegates lifecycle >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: OBSERVER + NOTIFICATION
' ====================================================================
interface OrderObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onOrderUpdate(order, event) : void
}

class CustomerNotificationObserver {
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    --
    + onOrderUpdate(order, event) : void
}

class RestaurantNotificationObserver {
    --
    + onOrderUpdate(order, event) : void
}

class DeliveryAgentObserver {
    --
    + onOrderUpdate(order, event) : void
}

OrderObserver <|.. CustomerNotificationObserver
OrderObserver <|.. RestaurantNotificationObserver
OrderObserver <|.. DeliveryAgentObserver
Order --> OrderObserver : notifies >

class NotificationService {
    - strategies : List<NotificationStrategy>
    --
    + notify(user, message) : void
}

interface NotificationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class EmailNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class SMSNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class PushNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

note bottom of OrderObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 7 - Everyone gets notified.**
    "On every state change, Order calls
    notifyObservers(). **Observer Pattern**:"
    "**CustomerObserver**: 'Your order is being prepared!'
    **RestaurantObserver**: 'New order received!'
    **DeliveryAgentObserver**: 'Pickup ready!'"

    "Notification channel via **Strategy**:
    Push, SMS, Email."
    **Patterns: Observer + Strategy | OCP, SRP**
end note

NotificationStrategy <|.. EmailNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. SMSNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. PushNotification
NotificationService --> NotificationStrategy : delegates >
CustomerNotificationObserver --> NotificationService : uses >
FoodOrderingService --> NotificationService


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: PAYMENT — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class PaymentService {
    --
    + processPayment(strategy, amount) : PaymentResult
}

interface PaymentStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + pay(amount) : PaymentResult
}

class CreditCardPayment {
    - cardNumber : String
    --
    + pay(amount) : PaymentResult
}

class UpiPayment {
    - upiId : String
    --
    + pay(amount) : PaymentResult
}

class WalletPayment {
    - walletId : String
    --
    + pay(amount) : PaymentResult
}

class CashOnDeliveryPayment {
    --
    + pay(amount) : PaymentResult
}

class PaymentResult {
    - success : boolean
    - transactionId : String
    - message : String
}

note bottom of PaymentStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 8 - Customer pays.**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — payment method
    is pluggable. CreditCard, UPI, Wallet,
    CashOnDelivery. Add PayPal? One class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP**
end note

PaymentStrategy <|.. CreditCardPayment
PaymentStrategy <|.. UpiPayment
PaymentStrategy <|.. WalletPayment
PaymentStrategy <|.. CashOnDeliveryPayment
PaymentService --> PaymentStrategy : delegates >
PaymentService --> PaymentResult : returns >
FoodOrderingService --> PaymentService


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 9: RATING
' ====================================================================
class RatingService {
    - ratings : Map<String, List<Rating>>
    --
    + addRating(orderId, customerId, restaurantId, score, review) : Rating
    + getAverageRating(restaurantId) : double
    + getRatings(restaurantId) : List<Rating>
    + getTopRated(limit) : List<Restaurant>
}

class Rating {
    - ratingId : String
    - customerId : String
    - restaurantId : String
    - orderId : String
    - score : int
    - review : String
    - createdAt : LocalDateTime
    --
    + getScore() : int
    + getReview() : String
}

note bottom of RatingService #B2EBF2
    **STEP 9 - User rates the restaurant.**
    "After delivery, user rates 1-5 stars
    and leaves a review. RatingService
    computes running average and updates
    Restaurant.averageRating."

    "Ratings feed back into SortByRating
    strategy — the system improves itself."
end note

RatingService --> Rating : manages >
Rating --> Customer
Rating --> Restaurant
FoodOrderingService --> RatingService


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Full journey: search restaurants (**Search Strategy**) ->
    sort results (**Sort Strategy**) -> add to cart -> place order (**Builder**)
    -> pay (**Payment Strategy**) -> order transitions Placed->Confirmed
    ->Preparing->OutForDelivery->Delivered (**State Pattern**) -> customer,
    restaurant, rider notified at each step (**Observer + Notification Strategy**)
    -> user rates restaurant (**Rating**).
    6 patterns: **Facade**, **Strategy** (x4), **Composite**, **State**, **Observer**, **Builder**."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | User opens app, calls FoodOrderingService | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | Customer, Restaurant, MenuItem, Address models | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Search: by name, cuisine, location, or chained | Strategy + Composite | OCP, DIP |
    | 4 | Sort: by rating, price, distance, delivery time | Strategy + Composite | OCP |
    | 5 | Add to cart, place order via Builder | Builder | SRP |
    | 6 | Placed -> Confirmed -> Preparing -> Delivering -> Delivered | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 7 | Customer, restaurant, delivery agent all notified | Observer + Strategy | OCP, SRP |
    | 8 | Pay via CreditCard / UPI / Wallet / COD | Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP |
    | 9 | Rate restaurant 1-5 stars, feeds back into sort | -- | SRP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Search + Sort** = Steps 3-4 | **Order + Pay** = Steps 5-6,8 | **Notify + Rate** = Steps 7,9 |  |
endlegend

@enduml
